30/09/2010
ATHENS, Greece -- The financial police arrested 20 people on Wednesday (September 29th) in an operation targeting an illegal cigarette plant in Khalkidhiki. Three of the arrested are Bulgarians, and the rest are Greek. A total of 60 tonnes of tobacco were seized. Cigarettes produced in the illegal facility are believed to have been sold in Western Europe for the past two years. (AFP, BGNES, Focus - 29/09/10)
